<qti-assessment-item xmlns="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0" xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" identifier="Q26_v4" title="Q26_v4" time-dependent="false" adaptive="false" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0 https://purl.imsglobal.org/spec/qti/v3p0/schema/xsd/imsqti_asiv3p0_v1p0.xsd">
  <qti-response-declaration identifier="RESPONSE" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier">
    <qti-correct-response>
      <qti-value>ChoiceB</qti-value>
    </qti-correct-response>
  </qti-response-declaration>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="FEEDBACK" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="SOLUTION" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="SCORE" cardinality="single" base-type="float"><qti-default-value><qti-value>0</qti-value></qti-default-value></qti-outcome-declaration><qti-item-body>
    <p>El costo de producción de un artículo se descompone en dos centros de costo, ambos en función de la cantidad de unidades producidas <m:math><m:mi>x</m:mi></m:math>:</p>
    <div>
      <p>
        <m:math>
          <m:mi>M</m:mi><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>)</m:mo>
          <m:mo>=</m:mo>
          <m:mn>820</m:mn><m:mi>x</m:mi>
          <m:mo>+</m:mo>
          <m:mn>120&#160;000</m:mn>
        </m:math>
        
        (costo de materiales)
      </p>
      <p>
        <m:math>
          <m:mi>L</m:mi><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>)</m:mo>
          <m:mo>=</m:mo>
          <m:mn>680</m:mn><m:mi>x</m:mi>
          <m:mo>+</m:mo>
          <m:mn>95&#160;000</m:mn>
        </m:math>
        
        (costo de mano de obra)
      </p>
    </div>
    <p>El costo total se modela como la suma de estos dos costos, es decir,
      <m:math>
        <m:msub><m:mi>C</m:mi><m:mi>T</m:mi></m:msub><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>)</m:mo>
        <m:mo>=</m:mo>
        <m:mi>M</m:mi><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>)</m:mo>
        <m:mo>+</m:mo>
        <m:mi>L</m:mi><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>)</m:mo>
      </m:math>.
      
      ¿Cuál de las siguientes expresiones representa una combinación consistente de términos semejantes para el costo total?
    </p>
    <qti-choice-interaction response-identifier="RESPONSE" shuffle="false" max-choices="1">
      
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceA">
        <m:math>
          <m:msub><m:mi>C</m:mi><m:mi>T</m:mi></m:msub><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>)</m:mo>
          <m:mo>=</m:mo>
          <m:mn>1500</m:mn><m:mi>x</m:mi>
          <m:mo>+</m:mo>
          <m:mn>25&#160;000</m:mn>
        </m:math>
        <qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceA" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. Al sumar los términos semejantes se obtiene 820x + 680x = 1&#160;500x y 120&#160;000 + 95&#160;000 = 215&#160;000. Por lo tanto, el costo total es 1&#160;500x + 215&#160;000, no 1&#160;500x + 25&#160;000.</qti-feedback-inline>
      </qti-simple-choice>
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceB">
        <m:math>
          <m:msub><m:mi>C</m:mi><m:mi>T</m:mi></m:msub><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>)</m:mo>
          <m:mo>=</m:mo>
          <m:mn>1500</m:mn><m:mi>x</m:mi>
          <m:mo>+</m:mo>
          <m:mn>215&#160;000</m:mn>
        </m:math>
        <qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceB" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">¡Correcto! La suma de los costos es (820x + 120&#160;000) + (680x + 95&#160;000). Entonces, 820x + 680x = 1&#160;500x y 120&#160;000 + 95&#160;000 = 215&#160;000. Así, el costo total queda 1&#160;500x + 215&#160;000.</qti-feedback-inline>
      </qti-simple-choice>
      
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceC">
        <m:math>
          <m:msub><m:mi>C</m:mi><m:mi>T</m:mi></m:msub><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>)</m:mo>
          <m:mo>=</m:mo>
          <m:mn>140</m:mn><m:mi>x</m:mi>
          <m:mo>+</m:mo>
          <m:mn>215&#160;000</m:mn>
        </m:math>
        <qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceC" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. Los términos con x se suman, no se restan: 820x + 680x = 1&#160;500x. El término independiente sí es 120&#160;000 + 95&#160;000 = 215&#160;000. Por eso, la expresión correcta no es 140x + 215&#160;000, sino 1&#160;500x + 215&#160;000.</qti-feedback-inline>
      </qti-simple-choice>
      
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceD">
        <m:math>
          <m:msub><m:mi>C</m:mi><m:mi>T</m:mi></m:msub><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>)</m:mo>
          <m:mo>=</m:mo>
          <m:mn>1500</m:mn><m:mi>x</m:mi>
          <m:mo>-</m:mo>
          <m:mn>215&#160;000</m:mn>
        </m:math>
        <qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceD" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. El enunciado indica que el costo total es la suma de ambos costos. Entonces, los términos independientes se suman: 120&#160;000 + 95&#160;000 = 215&#160;000. Por eso debe aparecer + 215&#160;000 y no − 215&#160;000.</qti-feedback-inline>
      </qti-simple-choice>
    </qti-choice-interaction>
    <qti-feedback-block identifier="show" outcome-identifier="SOLUTION" show-hide="show">
      <qti-content-body>
        <p><strong>Resolución paso a paso</strong></p>
        <ol>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 1: Escribir la suma de los dos costos</strong></p>
            <p>Como el costo total es la suma del costo de materiales y del costo de mano de obra, se tiene:</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:msub><m:mi>C</m:mi><m:mi>T</m:mi></m:msub><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>)</m:mo>
                <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                <m:mo>(</m:mo>
                <m:mn>820</m:mn><m:mi>x</m:mi>
                <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                <m:mn>120&#160;000</m:mn>
                <m:mo>)</m:mo>
                <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                <m:mo>(</m:mo>
                <m:mn>680</m:mn><m:mi>x</m:mi>
                <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                <m:mn>95&#160;000</m:mn>
                <m:mo>)</m:mo>
              </m:math>
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 2: Agrupar términos semejantes</strong></p>
            <p>Se agrupan los términos con <m:math><m:mi>x</m:mi></m:math> y los términos independientes:</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:msub><m:mi>C</m:mi><m:mi>T</m:mi></m:msub><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>)</m:mo>
                <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                <m:mo>(</m:mo>
                <m:mn>820</m:mn><m:mi>x</m:mi>
                <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                <m:mn>680</m:mn><m:mi>x</m:mi>
                <m:mo>)</m:mo>
                <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                <m:mo>(</m:mo>
                <m:mn>120&#160;000</m:mn>
                <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                <m:mn>95&#160;000</m:mn>
                <m:mo>)</m:mo>
              </m:math>
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 3: Sumar los coeficientes de <m:math><m:mi>x</m:mi></m:math></strong></p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mn>820</m:mn><m:mi>x</m:mi>
                <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                <m:mn>680</m:mn><m:mi>x</m:mi>
                <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                <m:mo>(</m:mo>
                <m:mn>820</m:mn>
                <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                <m:mn>680</m:mn>
                <m:mo>)</m:mo>
                <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                <m:mn>1500</m:mn><m:mi>x</m:mi>
              </m:math>
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 4: Sumar los términos independientes</strong></p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mn>120&#160;000</m:mn>
                <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                <m:mn>95&#160;000</m:mn>
                <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                <m:mn>215&#160;000</m:mn>
              </m:math>
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 5: Escribir la expresión final</strong></p>
            <p>Reemplazando los resultados obtenidos:</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:msub><m:mi>C</m:mi><m:mi>T</m:mi></m:msub><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>)</m:mo>
                <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                <m:mn>1500</m:mn><m:mi>x</m:mi>
                <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                <m:mn>215&#160;000</m:mn>
              </m:math>
            </p>
            <p>Por lo tanto, la alternativa correcta es <strong>ChoiceB</strong>.</p>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </qti-content-body>
    </qti-feedback-block>
  </qti-item-body>
  <qti-response-processing>
    <qti-response-condition>
      <qti-response-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceB</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SCORE">
          <qti-base-value base-type="float">1</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceB</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceC</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceC</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceD</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceD</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else>
    </qti-response-condition>
  </qti-response-processing>
</qti-assessment-item>